    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nRelated to https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/7240, when formatting a Unicode character value with the `:c` format and short padding (< 250 characters), Cython can generate code that builds an incorrect string. This is due to an off-by-one error in the `CIntToPyUnicode` utility code that inserts a spurious character (from potentially uninitialised memory) before the formatted character.\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/e16ba11fc555c42afee71e5722828a6dd06eb12e/Cython/Utility/TypeConversion.c#L936-L938\n\nThe bug was introduced in commit https://github.com/cython/cython/commit/e1c98faaf7c6d1c92d02644046a2f5a63195a803 from PR https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/6342\n\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\n# The following generates e.g. the string \"    \\x00x\" instead of the expected \"    x\"\nassert f\"{ord('x'):5c\" == \"    x\"\n```\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\n_No response_\n\n### OS\n\n_No response_\n\n### Python version\n\n_No response_\n\n### Cython version\n\nCython 3.1+\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
